---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="React" description="Rizzo CSS components and examples for React.">
  <section>
    <h2>React</h2>
    <p>
      Use Rizzo CSS in your React app. The design system is built with a <strong>CSS-first</strong> architecture:
      the same BEM class names and styles work across Astro, Svelte, React, Vue, and Vanilla.
    </p>
    <h3>Setup</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Install the package: <code>pnpm add rizzo-css</code> (or npm/yarn).</li>
      <li>Import the main CSS in your app entry (e.g. <code>main.tsx</code>): <code>import 'rizzo-css'</code>.</li>
      <li>Copy React components from this repo (<code>src/components/react/</code>) into your project, or use the examples on each component page.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      React components use the same class names as the Astro and Svelte versions, so they look and behave the same.
    </p>
    <h3>Components</h3>
    <p>
      <a href="/docs/react/components">Browse all 50 React components</a> — each has a full implementation, live demo, and React/TSX code blocks. Start with <a href="/docs/react/components/button">Button</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Other frameworks:</strong> <a href="/docs">Astro</a> · <a href="/docs/svelte">Svelte</a> · <a href="/docs/vue">Vue</a> · <a href="/docs/vanilla">Vanilla</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
